      "methods": [],
      "module_path": "task_contract",
      "docs": "A single coverage-verification violation found during `bin/sotp task-contract coverage`. The coverage command owns attribution completeness, referential integrity, and fail-closed availability of per-layer type-signals.json inputs; the separate `check` command owns liveness/non-blue signal evaluation. MissingTaskContract: task-contract.json is absent so coverage cannot check anything (fail-closed). OrphanEntry: a catalogue entry exists but is not attributed to any task in task-contract.json (attribution completeness failure). InvalidEntryRef: an entry attributed in task-contract.json does not exist in the current catalogue (referential integrity failure). InvalidEntryRef.reason is an opaque diagnostic string (R9 exception: error message). MissingSignalDocument: the per-layer type-signals.json document is absent for a canonical TDDD layer; emitted regardless of attribution presence so that coverage fails closed when a signal document cannot be found. InvalidTaskRef: a task key in task-contract.json entries map is not present in impl-plan.json task IDs (referential integrity failure per D9/IN-11); task_id is the stale TaskId and entry_keys carries all ContractedEntryRef entries attributed under it. Coverage fails closed whenever any InvalidTaskRef exists. These violations are data inside CoverageVerifyOutcome::Blocked.",
      "spec_refs": [
        { "file": "track/items/pre-review-task-contract-conformance-gate-2026-06-27/spec.json", "anchor": "IN-03" },
        { "file": "track/items/pre-review-task-contract-conformance-gate-2026-06-27/spec.json", "anchor": "IN-07" },
